Rating: 4
I've been making this since it first appeared in Gourmet in 1995. It had been a while, and decided to make this last weekend for a dinner party; specifically for a guest who didn't care for fruit desserts. I baked it for 35 minutes on convection. It was perfectly done; moist in the center with a great texture. One of my guests was a former restaurant owner, and he was impressed with this. Highly recommended for any event where you want to have a show-stopping dessert. I'm making it again today!

Rating: 4
I was looking through my recipe box for a dessert and noticed that I've had this recipe for almost 10 years, now. I have made this over and over and over again. I've given tortes as gifts, brought them to parties and birthdays, and it's been the signature dessert for my Thanksgiving dinner every year. My family goes NUTS for this torte. My friends think I should SELL these tortes. I've made them with chopped hazelnuts on top, ground hazelnuts on top, no nuts on top, swirly designs, smooth and flat, if I can dream it up, I've done it. It is incredibly good with whipped cream. It is fantastic all by itself. It's not too sweet. I absolutely reduce the baking temp to 360 and bake for 40 minutes only. It freezes perfectly. Best of all, it is very easy. The first time I made it, I was pretty inexperienced and I made it with no trouble and it turned out perfectly. Now I can practically do this with my eyes closed. So thanks Gourmet! And yes, I WILL be making this again!

