Rating: 4
I've made this for several dinner parties. Good cooks beg for the recipe, and non-cooks just sit in wonder, it's that good! Not sickeningly sweet, unlike most chocolate desserts. Personal observations: if I don't reduce the cooking time 5 minutes below the recommended minimum, and also reduce the temp by 15 degrees, it comes out too dry. Several attempts show that the more moist, the better. Also, the glaze takes a LOT longer to set than the recipe says, unless you want to just let it drip down the sides and not adhere at all.

